Dear [CEO Name],\
\
I'm writing to share something I believe could meaningfully change how our communications department operates and what we're able to deliver for HAP.\
\

\f1\b What I've built.
\f0\b0  Using cutting-edge AI-assisted development tools (Cursor), I've created interactive web dashboards that turn our Pennsylvania hospital reports into engaging, explorable experiences. Legislators and hospital leaders can now click through data, toggle policy scenarios, and understand complex findings in minutes instead of reading lengthy PDFs. This isn't a prototype. It\'92s working, branded, and ready to support our advocacy and member communications.\
\

\f1\b Why this matters.
\f0\b0  Our reports are authoritative and data-rich, but they're also dense. Busy lawmakers and executives often don't have time to absorb 50-page analyses. Interactive dashboards solve that: they meet people where they are, let them explore what matters to them, and make our message stick. The same content that used to live only in static documents can now be shared in meetings, embedded in emails, or linked from social without losing rigor or credibility.\
\

\f1\b What it required.
\f0\b0  This work demanded more than technical skill. It required understanding our policy goals, our audience, and our brand then translating that into clear structure, compelling visuals, and intuitive interactions. AI tools don't replace judgment; they amplify it. Knowing what to ask for, how to refine outputs, and when to push back on suggestions is where human intelligence remains irreplaceable. I've learned to work with these tools as a force multiplier: I set direction, ensure accuracy, and maintain our standards while moving faster than we could before.\
\

\f1\b The opportunity.
\f0\b0  I'm one person in communications, and I've already produced two distinct dashboards. Imagine what becomes possible if we lean into this: faster turnaround on data-driven campaigns, more engaging member resources, and a communications function that can respond to policy windows with polished, interactive materials in days instead of weeks. The tools are here. The question is whether we choose to use them strategically.\
\
I'm not asking for anything formal in this email only to put this on your radar. I'd welcome the chance to show you what I've built and discuss how we might scale this approach across the organization.\
\
Thank you for your time and leadership.\
\
Best regards,\
